1. Configurar acesso ao cluster



2. Escolha o chart Wordpress

https://artifacthub.io/packages/helm/bitnami/wordpress


3. Adicionar o repo

helm repo add estag https://charts.bitnami.com/bitnami
helm repo update


4. Escolher os parâmetros 

persistence.enabled=false
ingress.enabled=true
ingress.hostname="edison.stag.jac.bsb.br"
resources.requests=null
mariadb.primary.persistence.enable=false


5. Instalar o pacote

helm install wp-edison/estag/wordpress --create-namespace -n edison-krause --set persistence.enabled=false --set ingress.enabled=true --set ingress.hostname="wp-edison.stag.jac.bsb.br" --set resources.requests=null --set mariadb.primary.persistence.enable=false

-> comando correto,
helm install wp-edison-krause estag/wordpress --create-namespace -n edison-krause --set persistence.enabled=false --set ingress.enabled=true --set ingress.hostname="wp-edison-krause.stag.jac.bsb.br" --set resources.requests=null --set mariadb.primary.persistence.enabled=false


6. Atualizar ou reconfigurar

helm get values wp-<SEU NOME> -n <SEU NAMESPACE>

Consultar os parâmetros atuais da release


7. Rollback!!!

helm rollback wp-edison-krause -n edison-krause


8 - Desinstalar!!

helm uninstall wp-edison-krause -n edison-krause

---

ingress:
  enabled: true
  hostname: wp-<SEU NOME>.stag.jac.bsb.br
mariadb:
  primary:
    persistence:
      enabled: false
persistence:
  enabled: false
resources:
  requests: null


Criar arquivos values e modificar parâmetro desejado
Executar o upgrade

USER-SUPPLIED VALUES:
ingress:
  enabled: true
  hostname: wp-edison-krause.stag.jac.bsb.br
mariadb:
  primary:
    persistence:
      enabled: false
persistence:
  enabled: false
resources:
  requests: null
  